Look at this. As you deal

00:18:18.120 --> 00:18:20.750
with that stuff, and when John read that

00:18:20.760 --> 00:18:25.990
little bit

00:18:25.990 --> 00:18:26.000
about

00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:27.830
what he said about leadership and

00:18:27.840 --> 00:18:29.870
about the fatherless, what I

00:18:29.870 --> 00:18:29.880
have

00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:32.630
always gone about the fatherless, the

00:18:37.560 --> 00:18:39.070
body of Christ that does not have a

00:18:39.080 --> 00:18:40.350
dad, there

00:18:40.350 --> 00:18:40.360
are

00:18:40.360 --> 00:18:42.910
a lot of fatherless children out

00:18:42.920 --> 00:18:45.670
there that need this. I felt like a

00:18:45.680 --> 00:18:49.070
lot of times, this

00:18:49.080 --> 00:18:51.190
part of this chapter spoke so loud to

00:18:51.200 --> 00:18:53.150
me. So I thought if it

00:18:53.160 --> 00:18:55.350
spoke so loud to me, maybe it would help

00:18:55.360 --> 00:18:56.510
you

00:18:56.520 --> 00:18:58.950
because there are certain things that she

00:18:58.960 --> 00:19:00.990
said today. Go ahead and just read some

00:19:01.000 --> 00:19:02.550
of that. It is really good.

00:19:17.520 --> 00:19:19.590
I have seen this cry. So, it

00:19:19.590 --> 00:19:19.600
says,

00:19:19.600 --> 00:19:21.790
Where are the fathers? I have seen

00:19:21.800 --> 00:19:23.790
this cry in countless men and women in

00:19:23.800 --> 00:19:25.350
the body of Christ. Most of them are

00:19:25.360 --> 00:19:27.510
young and with a strong call of God on

00:19:27.520 --> 00:19:29.270
their lives. They cry out for a father,

00:19:29.280 --> 00:19:31.150
a man to disciple, love, support, and

00:19:31.160 --> 00:19:33.310
encourage them. This is why God said

00:19:33.320 --> 00:19:34.750
that he would turn the hearts of the

00:19:34.760 --> 00:19:36.390
fathers, the leaders to the children,

00:19:36.400 --> 00:19:37.670
the people, and the hearts of the

00:19:37.680 --> 00:19:40.150
children to their fathers, lest I come

00:19:40.160 --> 00:19:42.350
and strike the earth with a curse.

00:19:42.360 --> 00:19:45.110
Malachi 4:6. Our nation lost its

00:19:45.120 --> 00:19:46.830
fathers, dads, leaders, or ministers in

00:19:46.840 --> 00:19:49.270
the 1940s and 1950s, and today our

00:19:49.280 --> 00:19:51.790
condition is getting worse. Not unlike

00:19:51.800 --> 00:19:53.630
Saul, many leaders in our homes,

00:19:53.640 --> 00:19:56.110
corporations, and churches are more

00:19:56.120 --> 00:19:58.150
concerned with their goals than with

00:19:58.160 --> 00:20:00.030
their offspring.

00:20:00.040 --> 00:20:02.230
Because of this attitude, these leaders

00:20:02.240 --> 00:20:04.390
view God's people as resources to serve

00:20:04.400 --> 00:20:06.310
their vision instead of seeing the

00:20:06.320 --> 00:20:08.390
vision as the vehicle to serve the

00:20:08.400 --> 00:20:09.630
people.

00:20:09.640 --> 00:20:12.190
The success of the vision justifies the

00:20:12.200 --> 00:20:14.110
cost of wounded lives and shattered

00:20:14.120 --> 00:20:17.550
people. Justice, mercy, integrity, and

00:20:17.560 --> 00:20:20.710
love are compromised for success.

00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:23.710
Decisions are based on money, numbers,

00:20:23.720 --> 00:20:26.350
and results. This opens the door to

00:20:26.360 --> 00:20:28.710
treatment such as David received. After

00:20:28.720 --> 00:20:31.470
all, Saul had a kingdom to protect. This

00:20:31.480 --> 00:20:33.310
type of treatment is acceptable in the

00:20:33.310 --> 00:20:33.320
leaders'minds

00:20:33.320 --> 00:20:35.310
because they are pursuing

00:20:35.320 --> 00:20:37.710
the furtherance of the gospel. How many

00:20:37.720 --> 00:20:39.430
leaders have cut off men under them

00:20:39.440 --> 00:20:41.550
because of suspicion? Why are those

00:20:41.560 --> 00:20:43.870
leaders suspicious? Because they are not

00:20:43.880 --> 00:20:46.790
serving God. They are serving a vision.

00:20:46.800 --> 00:20:48.550
Like Saul, they are insecure in their

00:20:48.560 --> 00:20:50.190
calling and that breeds jealousy and

00:20:50.200 --> 00:20:52.270
pride. They recognize qualities in

00:20:52.280 --> 00:20:54.630
people that they know are godly and

00:20:54.640 --> 00:20:56.350
they are willing to use those people as

00:20:56.360 --> 00:20:58.430
long as it benefits them.

00:20:58.440 --> 00:21:00.870
Saul enjoyed the success of David until

00:21:00.880 --> 00:21:02.910
he saw it as a threat to him. Then he

00:21:02.920 --> 00:21:04.750
demoted David and watched for a reason

00:21:04.760 --> 00:21:06.790
to destroy him.

00:21:06.800 --> 00:21:08.910
I have talked through with

00:21:08.920 --> 00:21:10.830
countless young men and women who cried

00:21:10.840 --> 00:21:12.790
out for accountability. They wanted to

00:21:12.800 --> 00:21:14.070
be submitted to a leader who would

00:21:14.080 --> 00:21:15.750
disciple them. They felt

00:21:15.760 --> 00:21:17.910
isolated and alone. They were seeking

00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:20.230
someone to father them. But God allowed

00:21:20.240 --> 00:21:22.350
them to go through rejection because God

00:21:22.360 --> 00:21:24.470
wanted to do in them what he had done in

00:21:24.480 --> 00:21:25.990
David.

00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:27.590
Listen carefully to what the Spirit

00:21:27.600 --> 00:21:29.590
is saying.

00:21:29.600 --> 00:21:31.790
David was concerned that Saul

00:21:31.800 --> 00:21:33.990
believed he was rebellious and evil.

00:21:34.000 --> 00:21:35.350
David must have searched his heart

00:21:35.360 --> 00:21:37.510
saying, Where have I gone wrong? How

00:21:37.520 --> 00:21:39.550
was Saul's heart turned against me so

00:21:39.560 --> 00:21:41.910
quickly? That is why he cried out,

00:21:41.920 --> 00:21:43.870
Someone urged me to kill you, but I

00:21:43.880 --> 00:21:46.470
said no. I only cut off the corner of

00:21:46.480 --> 00:21:48.870
your robe so that you could know and see

00:21:48.880 --> 00:21:51.390
that there is neither evil nor rebellion

00:21:51.400 --> 00:21:55.190
in my hand. See 1st Samuel 24. David

00:21:55.200 --> 00:21:57.870
thought if he could prove his love for

00:21:57.880 --> 00:22:00.310
Saul, Saul would restore him to favor and

00:22:00.320 --> 00:22:02.950
the prophecy would be fulfilled. People

00:22:02.960 --> 00:22:05.390
who have been rejected by a father or

00:22:05.400 --> 00:22:07.990
leader tend to take all the blame on

00:22:08.000 --> 00:22:10.110
themselves. They are imprisoned by

00:22:10.120 --> 00:22:12.750
tormenting thoughts of, What did I do? and,

00:22:12.760 --> 00:22:15.030
Was my heart impure? They sometimes

00:22:15.040 --> 00:22:16.950
wonder who turned the heart of my leader

00:22:16.960 --> 00:22:19.430
against me. Then they constantly try to

00:22:19.440 --> 00:22:21.550
prove their innocence to their leaders.

00:22:21.560 --> 00:22:23.390
They think that if they can only show

00:22:23.400 --> 00:22:25.110
their loyalty and value, they will be

00:22:25.120 --> 00:22:28.030
accepted. Sadly, the more they try, the

00:22:28.040 --> 00:22:31.630
more rejected they feel.

00:22:31.640 --> 00:22:34.030
So, I

00:22:34.030 --> 00:22:34.040
have

00:22:34.040 --> 00:22:36.590
dealt with this a lot.

00:22:36.600 --> 00:22:39.150
That paragraph right

00:22:39.160 --> 00:22:42.150
there is a summary of my life.

00:22:42.160 --> 00:22:44.710
I felt like when she read that to me,

00:22:44.720 --> 00:22:47.590
I was just

00:22:47.600 --> 00:22:52.470
going over this book, and

00:22:52.470 --> 00:22:52.480
it

00:22:52.480 --> 00:22:55.550
has helped me so much—the bait

00:22:55.550 --> 00:22:55.560
of Satan, and

00:22:55.560 --> 00:22:58.470
walking in

00:22:58.470 --> 00:22:58.480
offense

00:22:58.480 --> 00:23:01.310
towards leadership.

00:23:01.320 --> 00:23:03.830
Who I always talk about, you know, when

00:23:03.840 --> 00:23:05.630
I say, Where are the fathers? Where are the

00:23:05.640 --> 00:23:07.590
fathers of the faith? There is so much

00:23:07.600 --> 00:23:10.670
rejection, and in our

00:23:10.680 --> 00:23:12.670
case, the Lord has blessed us so much

00:23:12.680 --> 00:23:14.990
with so many people following us so

00:23:15.000 --> 00:23:17.990
quickly. It seems to be, the bigger

00:23:18.000 --> 00:23:20.710
it gets, the more rejection you receive

00:23:20.720 --> 00:23:22.630
from people. She brought up some

00:23:22.640 --> 00:23:24.350
other ministries. She said,

00:23:24.350 --> 00:23:24.360
Brandon,

00:23:24.360 --> 00:23:26.070
isn't it amazing? Have you ever seen so

00:23:26.070 --> 00:23:26.080
and so

00:23:26.080 --> 00:23:28.870
do a conference?

00:23:28.870 --> 00:23:28.880
They

00:23:28.880 --> 00:23:30.830
are

00:23:30.840 --> 00:23:33.310
always alone. Why?

00:23:33.310 --> 00:23:33.320
Because

00:23:33.320 --> 00:23:34.670
they have some of the biggest

00:23:34.680 --> 00:23:36.510
churches in Oklahoma.

00:23:36.520 --> 00:23:39.590
He has the biggest church in Oklahoma.

00:23:39.600 --> 00:23:42.070
He has plants

00:23:42.080 --> 00:23:44.750
around the whole world and he does

00:23:44.750 --> 00:23:44.760
not

00:23:44.760 --> 00:23:46.710
hang around this. And then

00:23:46.720 --> 00:23:47.990
she went over, do you know this

00:23:48.000 --> 00:23:50.270
pastor? And so we went over and

00:23:51.160 --> 00:23:55.270
I said, Isn't that interesting? They

00:23:55.270 --> 00:23:55.280
are

00:23:55.280 --> 00:23:58.430
criticized more than they are

00:23:59.040 --> 00:24:00.950
about what they are not doing or how they

00:24:00.950 --> 00:24:00.960
are

00:24:00.960 --> 00:24:03.870
not preaching right or whatever.

00:24:03.880 --> 00:24:05.990
And there is so much criticism towards

00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:09.950
it, but it comes out of a

00:24:11.000 --> 00:24:12.670
jealousy

00:24:12.680 --> 00:24:16.230
and an envy. People compare

00:24:16.240 --> 00:24:18.630
because they feel less than. And so I

00:24:18.630 --> 00:24:18.640
have

00:24:18.640 --> 00:24:21.870
realized as watching this, that is why

00:24:21.880 --> 00:24:22.950
some of these—because I always

00:24:22.950 --> 00:24:22.960
said,

00:24:22.960 --> 00:24:24.910
Why do they? When she brought that up

00:24:24.910 --> 00:24:24.920
today,

00:24:24.920 --> 00:24:25.990
she was talking to me about it.

00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:29.190
I said, Why do they do that? That

00:24:29.190 --> 00:24:29.200
is

00:24:29.200 --> 00:24:31.510
interesting, love. And we

00:24:31.520 --> 00:24:32.870
started going over it, and the Holy Spirit

00:24:32.880 --> 00:24:35.590
was ministering to me all day long.

00:24:35.600 --> 00:24:37.150
And then he was dealing with me

00:24:37.160 --> 00:24:38.430
with this kind of stuff. But we were

00:24:38.440 --> 00:24:41.230
praying for what is about to happen with

00:24:43.080 --> 00:24:46.750
Iran and the attacks on

00:24:46.760 --> 00:24:48.950
our soil,

00:24:48.960 --> 00:24:50.750
the storm that I feel is about to

00:24:50.760 --> 00:24:52.150
happen,

00:24:52.160 --> 00:24:53.990
that we are right at it. And when I went

00:24:53.990 --> 00:24:54.000
into

00:24:54.000 --> 00:24:56.430
the spirit, I have been very

00:24:56.440 --> 00:24:58.350
watchful

00:24:58.360 --> 00:25:00.590
over how I release things when I

00:25:00.590 --> 00:25:00.600
am

00:25:00.600 --> 00:25:03.470
seeing it even live. I hold things

00:25:03.480 --> 00:25:05.990
back a lot because of

00:25:08.400 --> 00:25:10.790
not feeling a release necessarily,

00:25:10.800 --> 00:25:13.230
because people cannot handle it, because

00:25:13.240 --> 00:25:15.590
you have such a variety of mature

00:25:15.600 --> 00:25:18.670
believers and immature believers.

00:25:18.680 --> 00:25:20.630
And so it is interesting

00:25:20.640 --> 00:25:22.590
because that is why I try to say,

00:25:22.600 --> 00:25:25.030
and maybe I come across harsh saying, there

00:25:25.030 --> 00:25:25.040
is

00:25:25.040 --> 00:25:27.150
99.9%

00:25:27.160 --> 00:25:28.830
of you that have no idea how to have a

00:25:28.840 --> 00:25:31.310
relationship with him. And

00:25:31.320 --> 00:25:33.350
the ones that are mature, because the mature

00:25:33.360 --> 00:25:36.070
believers go, Well, that is offensive.

00:25:36.080 --> 00:25:37.710
And they are doing exactly what I

00:25:37.710 --> 00:25:37.720
am

00:25:37.720 --> 00:25:39.550
talking about. Don't be offended. I

00:25:39.550 --> 00:25:39.560
am

00:25:39.560 --> 00:25:41.430
not trying to pick at you. I

00:25:41.430 --> 00:25:41.440
am

00:25:41.440 --> 00:25:44.390
saying I have a lot of people

00:25:44.400 --> 00:25:46.590
that do not have a clue anything about

00:25:46.600 --> 00:25:48.270
the spirit realm and you are trying to

00:25:48.280 --> 00:25:50.150
educate because there are no fathers teaching

00:25:50.160 --> 00:25:51.830
it at church. There is not a lot of

00:25:51.840 --> 00:25:54.710
spiritual backbone at church anymore.

00:25:54.720 --> 00:25:57.150
And I have noticed when I have a

00:25:57.160 --> 00:25:59.110
survey and I ask people, Where do

00:25:59.120 --> 00:26:00.190
you go to church? We

00:26:00.190 --> 00:26:00.200
do not

00:26:00.200 --> 00:26:01.590
go to church.

00:26:01.600 --> 00:26:03.270
We watch online. We are offended. We don't

00:26:03.280 --> 00:26:05.150
want to go to church. And I come

00:26:05.160 --> 00:26:07.670
across more like to the lady today. She

00:26:07.680 --> 00:26:09.550
went to church, a local church in

00:26:09.560 --> 00:26:12.510
Tulsa. And it is very seldom

00:26:12.520 --> 00:26:14.670
that I come across somebody that

00:26:14.670 --> 00:26:14.680
says,

00:26:14.680 --> 00:26:16.350
Well, I go to church. So, well,

00:26:16.360 --> 00:26:18.430
we do not go to church.

00:26:18.440 --> 00:26:20.030
Well, why? Well, because we were

00:26:20.040 --> 00:26:21.990
offended.

00:26:22.000 --> 00:26:24.470
And that is why I wanted to bring this

00:26:24.480 --> 00:26:26.270
to the body of Christ even more after

00:26:26.280 --> 00:26:28.310
the Lord dealt with me about it. There

00:26:28.310 --> 00:26:28.320
are

00:26:28.320 --> 00:26:30.510
so many fatherless children. There are so

00:26:30.520 --> 00:26:32.550
many people that are not in church anymore

00:26:32.550 --> 00:26:32.560
because

00:26:32.560 --> 00:26:33.830
they do not want to go to church. They

00:26:33.830 --> 00:26:33.840
are

00:26:33.840 --> 00:26:35.750
offended at the pastor. They're

00:26:35.760 --> 00:26:37.430
offended at the Christian. You know,

00:26:37.440 --> 00:26:40.550
brother, I don't need church anymore.

00:26:40.560 --> 00:26:43.110
I find it online. I teach. And I was one

00:26:43.120 --> 00:26:44.590
of those

00:26:44.600 --> 00:26:47.110
for 10 years. Diana and I wouldn't go

00:26:47.120 --> 00:26:49.430
anywhere because of Megan, and

00:26:49.440 --> 00:26:51.710
we said, Well,

00:26:51.720 --> 00:26:54.070
the last time the usher told us to get

00:26:54.080 --> 00:26:56.910
up and leave because she was disrupting

00:26:56.920 --> 00:26:58.630
service, I vowed I'd never step foot

00:26:58.640 --> 00:27:00.190
back in another church again until she

00:27:00.200 --> 00:27:02.390
was better.

00:27:02.400 --> 00:27:05.030
Because it was so humiliating already to

00:27:05.040 --> 00:27:07.190
come because we couldn't put her in

00:27:07.200 --> 00:27:09.950
children's church because of how bad she

00:27:09.960 --> 00:27:12.070
was when she was really overcoming. And

00:27:12.080 --> 00:27:13.870
when the usher asked us, say, She's a

00:27:13.880 --> 00:27:15.550
disruption in the service, sir. Can you

00:27:15.560 --> 00:27:17.110
please leave? And I vowed at that time,

00:27:17.120 --> 00:27:20.830
I told her, I said, I will never

00:27:20.840 --> 00:27:23.670
go back to church, and we didn't for 10

00:27:23.680 --> 00:27:25.550
years.

00:27:25.560 --> 00:27:28.190
We watched online only. And I'm just

00:27:28.200 --> 00:27:29.670
being really transparent. I'm just being

00:27:29.680 --> 00:27:31.190
real.

00:27:31.200 --> 00:27:33.470
And I said, You know what? Church

00:27:33.480 --> 00:27:36.030
isn't for us. We'll just watch TV. And

00:27:36.040 --> 00:27:38.590
I got so bitter and so offended in my

00:27:38.600 --> 00:27:39.870
heart about everybody in the body of

00:27:39.880 --> 00:27:41.110
Christ.

00:27:41.120 --> 00:27:44.430
And I let that wall of offense build a

00:27:44.440 --> 00:27:46.750
mountain

00:27:46.760 --> 00:27:48.430
until the Holy Spirit started stripping

00:27:48.440 --> 00:27:51.950
it down and I realized I was wrong.

00:27:51.960 --> 00:27:54.110
And yeah, that usher was rude,

00:27:54.120 --> 00:27:56.870
but he was just a cranky old man.

00:27:56.880 --> 00:28:00.350
I forgive him. And you move on.

00:28:00.360 --> 00:28:02.270
But I know there's a lot of

00:28:02.270 --> 00:28:02.280
you

00:28:02.280 --> 00:28:04.470
that walk in that

00:28:04.480 --> 00:28:06.150
offense.

00:28:06.160 --> 00:28:08.270
Well, you know, I was dealt this way. I

00:28:08.280 --> 00:28:10.070
was dealt that way. Why? Because I come

00:28:10.080 --> 00:28:12.310
across you all the time

00:28:12.320 --> 00:28:14.550
and people tell me I only watch

00:28:14.560 --> 00:28:17.190
online. I don't we are the church,

00:28:17.200 --> 00:28:19.630
brother. We don't need to go to church.

00:28:19.640 --> 00:28:25.110
But

00:28:25.120 --> 00:28:28.190
as I have read

00:28:28.200 --> 00:28:30.870
what Jesus said in Matthew 24

00:28:30.880 --> 00:28:33.030
that many will be offended in these last

00:28:33.040 --> 00:28:34.510
days,

00:28:34.510 --> 00:28:34.520
there

00:28:34.520 --> 00:28:36.950
will

00:28:36.960 --> 00:28:39.790
be many false prophets.

00:28:39.800 --> 00:28:42.870
And

00:28:42.880 --> 00:28:45.950
you start to put it together that the

00:28:45.960 --> 00:28:47.990
ones that are not being shepherded, the

00:28:48.000 --> 00:28:50.630
ones that are off in la-la

00:28:50.640 --> 00:28:52.350
land over here by themselves out of

00:28:52.360 --> 00:28:53.630
offense,

00:28:53.640 --> 00:28:55.430
that spirit of offense, that root of

00:28:55.440 --> 00:28:56.910
offense

00:28:56.920 --> 00:28:59.350
is what makes it where you don't have

00:28:59.360 --> 00:29:01.270
discerning.

00:29:01.280 --> 00:29:03.830
You're not hearing him

00:29:03.840 --> 00:29:05.670
because if you can't

00:29:05.680 --> 00:29:08.110
forgive your brother of his trespasses,

00:29:08.120 --> 00:29:09.830
the Father said he won't forgive you of

00:29:09.840 --> 00:29:11.350
yours.

00:29:11.360 --> 00:29:13.790
So, you've allowed that offense and that

00:29:13.800 --> 00:29:15.910
root of bitterness to come in your heart

00:29:15.920 --> 00:29:17.950
so much that I don't want to hear

00:29:17.960 --> 00:29:19.470
anybody at church. I'm not going to go

00:29:19.480 --> 00:29:21.550
around the flock anymore. And we did it.

00:29:21.560 --> 00:29:23.790
I'm telling you. And it took a breaking

00:29:23.800 --> 00:29:25.870
down, and I started going,

00:29:25.880 --> 00:29:27.310
and we went to Billy Burke meetings, and

00:29:27.320 --> 00:29:29.950
that's when we started getting free.

00:29:29.960 --> 00:29:31.710
And I'm telling you, after you go to

00:29:31.720 --> 00:29:33.430
these things and you get a touch

00:29:33.440 --> 00:29:35.230
from the Father and you get a drink, you

00:29:35.240 --> 00:29:37.710
go, Man, I could just go and be a part

00:29:37.720 --> 00:29:39.670
of congregation. And I'm telling you,

00:29:39.680 --> 00:29:41.030
Glorious and these some other places, I

00:29:41.040 --> 00:29:42.510
don't like to mention it because I don't

00:29:42.520 --> 00:29:43.550
want everybody saying, Hey, we're going

00:29:43.560 --> 00:29:45.670
to move there. I want you to follow

00:29:45.680 --> 00:29:46.910
the voice of God for yourself. Don't go

00:29:46.920 --> 00:29:48.510
to church somewhere just because I go to

00:29:48.520 --> 00:29:51.150
church there. I want you to go to

00:29:51.160 --> 00:29:52.630
the church where God has called you to

00:29:52.640 --> 00:29:54.350
go to church,

00:29:54.360 --> 00:29:56.310
you know? So, I stopped mentioning a lot

00:29:56.320 --> 00:29:58.110
of places that I'm at all the time

00:29:58.120 --> 00:30:00.270
because people try to move from all over

00:30:00.280 --> 00:30:02.030
and they move here. One man

00:30:02.040 --> 00:30:03.870
moved from Florida,

00:30:03.880 --> 00:30:05.230
was here for a couple weeks, said, You

00:30:05.240 --> 00:30:06.550
know, Brian, this isn't for me. I've

00:30:06.560 --> 00:30:08.550
got to move back home.

00:30:08.560 --> 00:30:10.630
And I thought,

00:30:10.640 --> 00:30:13.830
Wow, that was sad. He moved over 2,000

00:30:13.840 --> 00:30:15.750
miles,

00:30:15.760 --> 00:30:18.390
was here for a month, sold his house,

00:30:18.400 --> 00:30:20.790
sold everything to come where we were,

00:30:20.800 --> 00:30:22.750
and didn't like where we were because it

00:30:22.760 --> 00:30:24.950
wasn't for him, because he wanted to copycat

00:30:24.960 --> 00:30:26.590
everything what we're doing

00:30:26.600 --> 00:30:29.390
and moved back.

00:30:29.400 --> 00:30:31.430
I don't know if he was

00:30:31.440 --> 00:30:32.910
offended or not or disappointed or

00:30:32.920 --> 00:30:35.910
whatever, but moved his family back to

00:30:35.920 --> 00:30:37.750
the Orlando area,

00:30:37.760 --> 00:30:39.750
and it was amazing because I thought

00:30:39.760 --> 00:30:42.430
I got to watch really carefully

00:30:42.440 --> 00:30:44.630
what I say because there's so much influence

00:30:44.640 --> 00:30:46.830
in this channel that people will just

00:30:46.840 --> 00:30:49.070
pick up their stuff. One man

00:30:49.070 --> 00:30:49.080
moved

00:30:49.080 --> 00:30:50.550
from Chicago. These people, you

00:30:50.560 --> 00:30:52.310
just look at them going, Did God tell

00:30:52.320 --> 00:30:54.630
you to do that?

00:30:54.630 --> 00:30:54.640
Because

00:30:54.640 --> 00:30:55.750
they act miserable. What am I

00:30:55.760 --> 00:30:57.390
supposed to do now? Well, I don't know.

00:30:57.400 --> 00:30:59.110
I'm not your Holy Ghost.

00:30:59.120 --> 00:31:01.030
If he told you to do something, you're

00:31:01.040 --> 00:31:02.350
going to have instruction and you're

00:31:02.360 --> 00:31:04.230
going to know what he's told you to do.

00:31:04.240 --> 00:31:05.790
And that's what he went in this book.

00:31:05.800 --> 00:31:07.430
Diana was reading this book and going

00:31:07.440 --> 00:31:10.310
over things. So, just we're picking

00:31:10.320 --> 00:31:12.150
it like you would pick a chicken off a

00:31:12.160 --> 00:31:13.150
bone

00:31:13.150 --> 00:31:13.160
because

00:31:13.160 --> 00:31:15.230
I want to understand. I don't want to

00:31:15.240 --> 00:31:17.150
live in that.

00:31:17.160 --> 00:31:18.390
And so,

00:31:18.400 --> 00:31:19.790
with all the stuff that I

00:31:19.800 --> 00:31:21.390
overcome, y'all, we're all a work in

00:31:21.400 --> 00:31:22.830
progress. And I say it over and over and

00:31:22.840 --> 00:31:24.190
over again, but it's like when

00:31:24.200 --> 00:31:26.110
you're dealing with different levels,

00:31:26.120 --> 00:31:27.190
different devils, and you're dealing

00:31:27.200 --> 00:31:29.110
with all this stuff, you realize the

00:31:29.120 --> 00:31:31.710
pattern of offense will keep you out of

00:31:31.720 --> 00:31:34.550
the will of God.

00:31:34.560 --> 00:31:36.990
It will keep you in that place of

00:31:37.000 --> 00:31:40.350
lukewarm.

00:31:40.360 --> 00:31:43.030
And

00:31:43.040 --> 00:31:44.750
because you're

00:31:44.760 --> 00:31:47.990
always just so touchy, and

00:31:48.000 --> 00:31:50.110
you go from one place to another

00:31:50.120 --> 00:31:52.190
offended because of what they said to

00:31:52.200 --> 00:31:53.790
you, and you go to

00:31:53.800 --> 00:31:55.550
the next church and you're upset at

00:31:55.560 --> 00:31:57.510
them, and well, you know, they're just

00:31:57.520 --> 00:31:59.710
like the other people. And he talked

00:31:59.720 --> 00:32:01.670
about putting people at a standard. He

00:32:01.680 --> 00:32:03.030
goes, well, the world doesn't treat you

00:32:03.040 --> 00:32:04.590
that way.

00:32:04.600 --> 00:32:06.270
And I say, I used to say that all the

00:32:06.280 --> 00:32:09.030
time. I bet if I hung around Brad Pitt,

00:32:09.040 --> 00:32:11.350
he wouldn't be that way.

00:32:11.360 --> 00:32:14.470
Just being sarcastic.

00:32:14.480 --> 00:32:17.790
And you keep Why?

00:32:17.790 --> 00:32:17.800
Because

00:32:17.800 --> 00:32:19.670
what did John say in that book? He said

00:32:19.680 --> 00:32:21.310
it's because the standard that you

00:32:21.320 --> 00:32:24.190
keep the people.

00:32:24.200 --> 00:32:26.750
It's your expectation

00:32:26.760 --> 00:32:28.390
of them.

00:32:28.400 --> 00:32:29.910
What are you expecting of the body of

00:32:29.920 --> 00:32:31.790
Christ?

00:32:31.800 --> 00:32:34.630
You have them at a higher

00:32:34.640 --> 00:32:36.630
standard of what they should be

00:32:36.640 --> 00:32:38.670
than what the world would be right

00:32:38.680 --> 00:32:39.670
here.

00:32:39.680 --> 00:32:42.430
Go ahead.

00:32:42.440 --> 00:32:43.630
I

00:32:43.640 --> 00:32:45.070
realized that the love I was

00:32:45.080 --> 00:32:47.230
giving was being sown to the spirit and

00:32:47.240 --> 00:32:48.790
eventually I would reap those seeds of

00:32:48.800 --> 00:32:50.510
love. I didn't know from where, but I

00:32:50.520 --> 00:32:52.110
knew the harvest would come. No longer

00:32:52.120 --> 00:32:53.830
did I see it as a failure when love

00:32:53.840 --> 00:32:55.270
wasn't returned from the person I was

00:32:55.280 --> 00:32:57.470
giving it to. It freed me to love that

00:32:57.480 --> 00:32:59.510
person even more. If more Christians

00:32:59.510 --> 00:32:59.520
recognize

00:32:59.520 --> 00:33:01.070
this, they wouldn't give up

00:33:01.080 --> 00:33:03.310
and become offended. Usually, this is not

00:33:03.320 --> 00:33:05.350
the type of love we walk

00:33:05.360 --> 00:33:07.750
in. We walk in a selfish love that is

00:33:07.760 --> 00:33:09.150
easily disappointed when our

00:33:09.160 --> 00:33:12.070
expectations are not met. If I have

00:33:12.080 --> 00:33:14.390
expectations about certain persons,

00:33:14.400 --> 00:33:16.670
those people can let me down. They will

00:33:16.680 --> 00:33:18.350
disappoint me to the degree that they

00:33:18.360 --> 00:33:21.070
fall short of my expectations. But if I

00:33:21.080 --> 00:33:23.430
have no expectations about someone,

00:33:23.440 --> 00:33:25.550
anything given is a blessing and not

00:33:25.560 --> 00:33:28.150
something owed. We set ourselves up for

00:33:28.160 --> 00:33:30.110
offense when we require certain

00:33:30.120 --> 00:33:32.550
behaviors from those with whom we have

00:33:32.560 --> 00:33:35.670
relationships. The more we expect, the

00:33:35.680 --> 00:33:41.430
greater the potential offense.

00:33:41.440 --> 00:33:42.590
Yep.

00:33:42.600 --> 00:33:44.510
The greater the

00:33:44.520 --> 00:33:45.830
relationship, the greater the

00:33:45.840 --> 00:33:48.070
expectation, the greater the offense.

00:33:48.080 --> 00:33:50.390
And when you get around leadership, and

00:33:50.400 --> 00:33:51.790
that's what the Lord told me. He said

00:33:51.800 --> 00:33:53.190
even in this one,

00:33:53.200 --> 00:33:56.110
I

00:33:56.120 --> 00:33:57.950
don't want you

00:33:57.960 --> 00:34:00.830
to be friends with the pastors.

00:34:00.840 --> 00:34:05.150
I want you to honor them as pastors.

00:34:05.160 --> 00:34:06.950
They're not your friends. They're your

00:34:06.960 --> 00:34:08.710
pastors.

00:34:08.720 --> 00:34:11.270
There's so many people

00:34:11.280 --> 00:34:12.629
say, Well, if I need to go out to

00:34:12.639 --> 00:34:14.190
dinner with you, I want to know you

00:34:14.200 --> 00:34:15.550
and I want to hang out with you, let's

00:34:15.560 --> 00:34:17.790
fist bump and have a donut.

00:34:17.800 --> 00:34:20.110
But the more you get to know them,

00:34:20.110 --> 00:34:20.120
the

00:34:20.120 --> 00:34:22.190
more you realize that

00:34:22.200 --> 00:34:25.590
they're just as human as you are.

00:34:25.600 --> 00:34:27.669
And that's why I even told the people

00:34:27.679 --> 00:34:29.909
that we go, Hey, listen. I don't want

00:34:29.919 --> 00:34:31.710
to be your friend

00:34:31.720 --> 00:34:34.990
because you're my pastor.

00:34:35.000 --> 00:34:37.790
I want to separate the friendship from a

00:34:37.800 --> 00:34:40.470
pastor because the more you become my

00:34:40.480 --> 00:34:42.510
friend, it's harder for you to be my

00:34:42.520 --> 00:34:45.710
pastor.

00:34:45.720 --> 00:34:48.750
And you become too familiar with them

00:34:48.760 --> 00:34:51.990
and then you dishonor them.

00:34:52.000 --> 00:34:53.590
And that's the same thing with my

00:34:53.600 --> 00:34:55.629
friend Billy Burke.

00:34:56.720 --> 00:34:59.750
If you talk too much to

00:34:59.750 --> 00:34:59.760
them,

00:34:59.760 --> 00:35:01.310
you start looking at them as just a

00:35:01.320 --> 00:35:03.590
normal human being. But God put them in

00:35:03.600 --> 00:35:05.430
your life to be that iron

00:35:05.440 --> 00:35:07.990
sharpens iron and that mentor.

00:35:08.000 --> 00:35:09.990
There's a line that you don't

00:35:10.000 --> 00:35:12.070
cross even with joking with people. The

00:35:12.080 --> 00:35:13.790
Lord said always

00:35:13.800 --> 00:35:16.470
maintain an atmosphere of honor when

00:35:16.480 --> 00:35:18.230
you're talking to him.

00:35:18.240 --> 00:35:21.750
Do not dishonor him even if you feel

00:35:21.760 --> 00:35:23.630
well. I am just kidding around

00:35:23.640 --> 00:35:25.430
with you. That

00:35:25.430 --> 00:35:25.440
is

00:35:25.440 --> 00:35:28.070
why there is a place of honor

00:35:28.080 --> 00:35:30.030
that

00:35:30.040 --> 00:35:33.350
I try to keep; not that I am exalting a man

00:35:33.360 --> 00:35:36.110
of God, but I want to put

00:35:36.120 --> 00:35:38.150
that pastor in the place of, 'You are my

00:35:38.160 --> 00:35:40.190
pastor, you are not my

00:35:40.190 --> 00:35:40.200
friend.'Does

00:35:40.200 --> 00:35:41.550
that make sense? There are so

00:35:41.560 --> 00:35:44.550
many times that I see

00:35:44.560 --> 00:35:47.230
the

00:35:47.230 --> 00:35:47.240
congregation—even

00:35:47.240 --> 00:35:48.750
when I worked for that mega-church in

00:35:48.760 --> 00:35:50.870
Oklahoma City—always wanting to be

00:35:50.880 --> 00:35:53.430
the friend of the pastor. Let

00:35:53.430 --> 00:35:53.440
us

00:35:53.440 --> 00:35:55.630
go to lunch. Let

00:35:55.630 --> 00:35:55.640
us

00:35:55.640 --> 00:35:58.310
go have a golf game.

00:35:58.320 --> 00:36:00.590
I want to go with you to golf. Let

00:36:00.590 --> 00:36:00.600
us

00:36:00.600 --> 00:36:02.310
catch

00:36:02.320 --> 00:36:04.390
a movie

00:36:04.400 --> 00:36:06.030
or go to the gym and work out.

00:36:06.040 --> 00:36:08.030
They tried to find some kind of ground

00:36:08.040 --> 00:36:08.990
on

00:36:09.000 --> 00:36:11.910
how to relate.

00:36:11.920 --> 00:36:14.430
All of a sudden,

00:36:14.440 --> 00:36:17.910
that pastor they were

00:36:17.920 --> 00:36:19.470
teaching

00:36:19.480 --> 00:36:22.230
became no longer

00:36:22.240 --> 00:36:23.790
able to minister to them because they

00:36:23.800 --> 00:36:27.110
became too familiar with

00:36:27.110 --> 00:36:27.120
him

00:36:27.120 --> 00:36:29.630
and it becomes a toxic relationship

00:36:29.630 --> 00:36:29.640
very

00:36:29.640 --> 00:36:32.270
quickly.

00:36:32.270 --> 00:36:32.280
I

00:36:32.280 --> 00:36:35.430
am

00:36:35.440 --> 00:36:38.350
going through all the things

00:36:38.360 --> 00:36:41.510
that I have overcome. I have learned

00:36:41.520 --> 00:36:44.030
to pray and be an armor bearer, and

00:36:44.040 --> 00:36:46.190
the Lord said, 'Even where we are, sit on

00:36:46.200 --> 00:36:47.470
the back row

00:36:47.470 --> 00:36:47.480
and

00:36:47.480 --> 00:36:49.710
do what I have called you to do. It is not

00:36:49.720 --> 00:36:52.110
for you to have a platform here; it

00:36:52.110 --> 00:36:52.120
is

00:36:52.120 --> 00:36:54.950
for you to get refreshed and

00:36:54.960 --> 00:36:57.190
go dump out more. You have a

00:36:57.200 --> 00:36:58.590
platform;

00:36:58.600 --> 00:37:00.990
use

00:37:00.990 --> 00:37:01.000
it

00:37:01.000 --> 00:37:03.470
and minister to the millions.

00:37:03.480 --> 00:37:06.670
Your job is to get refreshed, drink,

00:37:06.680 --> 00:37:09.030
and have some substance so

00:37:09.040 --> 00:37:10.830
that you are refreshed and you walk away

00:37:10.840 --> 00:37:13.630
going, I can go on another day.'Because of

00:37:13.640 --> 00:37:16.230
the bombardment of growing and

00:37:16.240 --> 00:37:18.350
doing what God has called us to do, it

00:37:18.350 --> 00:37:18.360
is

00:37:18.360 --> 00:37:20.910
very interesting as

00:37:20.920 --> 00:37:22.830
you try to

00:37:25.800 --> 00:37:28.350
keep that equilibrium.

00:37:28.360 --> 00:37:30.230
Is that a good way to say it? It

00:37:30.230 --> 00:37:30.240
is

00:37:30.240 --> 00:37:31.990
an equilibrium. There

00:37:31.990 --> 00:37:32.000
are

00:37:32.000 --> 00:37:34.350
so many of you

00:37:34.360 --> 00:37:36.630
I know—because I have the emails

00:37:36.630 --> 00:37:36.640
and

00:37:36.640 --> 00:37:38.590
the conversations in

00:37:38.590 --> 00:37:38.600
public—that

00:37:38.600 --> 00:37:40.150
say, 'Hey, I am offended. I do not go

00:37:40.160 --> 00:37:41.550
to church anymore.'Well, where did the

00:37:41.560 --> 00:37:44.230
offense come in?

00:37:44.240 --> 00:37:46.950
How did that happen?

00:37:46.960 --> 00:37:49.150
'Well, they said this to me.'Did you

00:37:49.160 --> 00:37:53.230
get too familiar with them?

00:37:53.240 --> 00:37:55.390
Were you a friend to the pastor?

00:37:55.400 --> 00:37:57.390
Did you allow them to correct you?

00:37:57.400 --> 00:37:58.870
Because I am telling you, iron sharpens

00:37:58.880 --> 00:38:00.470
iron. When you see

00:38:00.470 --> 00:38:00.480
those

00:38:00.480 --> 00:38:02.950
sparks fly, it happens.

00:38:02.960 --> 00:38:04.350
If you are not being

00:38:04.360 --> 00:38:07.270
challenged to grow... Diana

00:38:13.480 --> 00:38:16.790
said, 'Brandon, the books that make me

00:38:16.800 --> 00:38:18.430
grow the most, like these ones, are the

00:38:18.440 --> 00:38:20.750
ones that I love.'They are the ones that

00:38:20.760 --> 00:38:23.190
challenge you, where you

00:38:23.200 --> 00:38:25.470
have to think about

00:38:25.470 --> 00:38:25.480
it

00:38:25.480 --> 00:38:27.230
for a little bit longer.

00:38:34.920 --> 00:38:36.070
You said, 'I want to throw it out

00:38:36.080 --> 00:38:37.030
the window when I

00:38:37.030 --> 00:38:37.040
am driving.'Yeah,

00:38:37.040 --> 00:38:38.510
they make you get mad and you

00:38:38.520 --> 00:38:39.990
go, 'That

00:38:39.990 --> 00:38:40.000
is

00:38:40.000 --> 00:38:41.030
trash, I do not want to do that

00:38:41.030 --> 00:38:41.040
anymore.'But it is

00:38:41.040 --> 00:38:43.550
sharpening, it

00:38:43.550 --> 00:38:43.560
is challenging,

00:38:43.560 --> 00:38:46.030
and it makes you self-examine.

00:38:49.480 --> 00:38:51.870
Judge not lest you be judged;

00:38:51.880 --> 00:38:54.670
you judge yourself and think,

00:38:54.680 --> 00:38:56.510
'Where does this fit me and where

00:38:56.520 --> 00:38:58.990
am I going wrong?'There

00:38:58.990 --> 00:38:59.000
is

00:38:59.000 --> 00:39:01.110
somebody who said they read this

00:39:01.120 --> 00:39:03.150
book four times a year

00:39:03.160 --> 00:39:04.710
because it keeps them on

00:39:04.720 --> 00:39:07.190
track from being offended.

00:39:11.160 --> 00:39:12.950
He said he reads it at the first

00:39:12.960 --> 00:39:16.030
of every quarter. I thought, 'That

00:39:16.030 --> 00:39:16.040
is

00:39:16.040 --> 00:39:16.950
a

00:39:16.950 --> 00:39:16.960
wow.'But

00:39:16.960 --> 00:39:19.470
it

00:39:19.470 --> 00:39:19.480
is

00:39:19.480 --> 00:39:21.390
how I

00:39:21.390 --> 00:39:21.400
am

00:39:21.400 --> 00:39:23.310
with the things the Lord has told

00:39:23.320 --> 00:39:25.910
me, even with deflecting and giving Him

00:39:25.920 --> 00:39:30.150
the glory. I realize

00:39:30.160 --> 00:39:32.390
that I am like an airplane that just

00:39:32.400 --> 00:39:34.150
got off course. Just a

00:39:34.160 --> 00:39:36.310
little bit. The more you stay off

00:39:36.320 --> 00:39:39.110
course, the more you are flying way over

00:39:39.120 --> 00:39:40.190
here.

00:39:40.200 --> 00:39:42.870
The Lord said, 'Brandon, I told you

00:39:42.880 --> 00:39:45.950
to do this, this, and this,'and I go,

00:39:45.960 --> 00:39:49.350
'Oh,

00:39:51.320 --> 00:39:54.110
forgive

00:39:54.110 --> 00:39:54.120
me.'He

00:39:54.120 --> 00:39:56.670
will

00:39:56.680 --> 00:39:57.990
instruct you about your

00:39:58.000 --> 00:39:59.950
giving,

